                            <comment id="464109" author="arshad512" created="Fri, 18 Jul 2025 02:09:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue was ...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+ [[ -e lustre/lquota/lquota.ko ]]&lt;br/&gt;
+ report_build_problem 7 &apos;Build of lustre/lquota/lquota.ko failed for: 5.14.0-427.31.1_lustre.el9.x86_64 (x86_64)&apos; &apos;Make sure the name and&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Script is looking for lustre/lquota/lquota - It should look for lustre/quota/lquota.ko. (no &apos;l&apos; in &apos;lquota&apos;) after lustre&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Already fixed by Shaun&apos;s patch&#160; &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/59409&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/59409&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
